JOHANNESBURG - Orlando Pirates Football Club confirmed on Thursday that winger Thabo Rakhale will move to Chippa United. Defenders, Diamond Thopola and Phetso Maphanga will join the Buccaneers from United as part of the deal. The club said on their website, “both players join the club with immediate effect and will be introduced to the coaching staff when training resumes on December 27.” READ: Stars outshine Pirates in Bethlehem “Maphanga is a defender who is in the mould of team captain Thabo Matlaba while Thopola, who was captain of the Chilly Boys is known for his no nonsense style of play.” The Soweto giants thanked Rakhale for his contribution at the club and wished him all of the best in his future endeavours. eNCA